Booking.com BV is the world’s #1 accommodation site and the 3rd largest global e-commerce player. The diverse team, 15,000 strong, is united by a single mission: to empower people to experience the world. We connect travelers with the world’s largest selection of incredible places to stay, including everything from apartments, vacation homes, and family-run B&Bs to 5-star luxury resorts, tree houses and even igloos. Each day, more than 1,200,000 room nights are reserved on our platform.

At Booking.com we aim to provide all of our guests with the widest choice of experiences at the best possible prices. The Partnerships team focuses on bringing these offerings to businesses of any size that need to tap into any travel related content or inventory anywhere in the world. In order to do so we engage with existing and future distribution partners to realize this goal. 

To support this strategy, we have created a dedicated team within our Partnerships department: Commercial Excellence. The main responsibility of this team is to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of the commercial organization within the Partnerships department, in order to accelerate its growth and increase its profitability.

The main responsibility of this role is to support our local teams and drive strategic change to become an effective channel for our distribution partners to engage with. It involves providing relevant, action oriented and innovative recommendations to our regional teams as well as global stakeholders to result in tangible commercial and operational improvements. This responsibility runs across all product lines within the Partnerships Department (= Affiliates, Corporates, AffNets, App Distro and Transportation).
