The role:
This is a full-time position based in our New York City office, also open to being based in Toronto, Canada or Grand Rapids, MI. In this position you will be part of an international team, consisting of colleagues who manage payroll for the Booking.com group offices in Europe, Middle East, Africa, Latin America and Asia. You will be reporting to the Americas Payroll Manager.
You will be responsible for managing a portfolio in the NORAM Region.
Main responsibilities:
Be responsible for the maintenance and preparation of payrolls. The employment mutations are provided by HR team and employees in the various countries;
Coordinate and finalize payrolls for payment approvals with the support of third party stakeholders;
Ensure efficient and high-quality execution of payroll processes and meet the deadlines;
Ensure compliance of all statutory payroll related tax filings and payments are made;
Prepare bi weekly and monthly payroll reconciliations;
Develop ad hoc financial and operational reports as needed;
Attend to payroll specific queries from employees;
Safeguard payroll procedures & internal controls and support requests from audit partner;
Undertake any ad hoc projects, as required.
